From: AWS-LC integration CI <aws-lc-ci@amazon.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Gate builtin sha2 typedefs on K5_BUILTIN_SHA2

When krb5 is built against AWS-LC with --with-crypto-impl=openssl,
crypto_int.h sets K5_OPENSSL_SHA2 (i.e., K5_BUILTIN_SHA2 is *not*
defined), so the bodies of sha256.c and sha512.c compile to nothing
under their #ifdef K5_BUILTIN_SHA2 guards.

However, the lib/crypto/builtin/sha2/ subdirectory is still built
unconditionally, and sha2.h's struct definitions plus
`typedef struct ... SHA{256,512}_CTX` are unguarded. AWS-LC's
<openssl/opensslv.h> transitively includes <openssl/base.h>, which
defines its own SHA256_CTX and SHA512_CTX typedefs. Because
crypto_int.h pulls in <openssl/opensslv.h> when CRYPTO_OPENSSL is
set, the typedefs collide:

    sha2.h:62: error: conflicting types for 'SHA256_CTX'
    sha2.h:64: error: conflicting types for 'SHA512_CTX'

(Stock OpenSSL's <openssl/opensslv.h> only contains version macros,
so it does not include base.h, and the conflict does not arise.)

Gate the struct/typedef block in sha2.h on K5_BUILTIN_SHA2 to match
the bodies of sha256.c/sha512.c. This is a no-op for the builtin
build and resolves the typedef collision when building against
AWS-LC.

---
 src/lib/crypto/builtin/sha2/sha2.h | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/lib/crypto/builtin/sha2/sha2.h b/src/lib/crypto/builtin/sha2/sha2.h
index 3aebd3e..8313203 100644
--- a/src/lib/crypto/builtin/sha2/sha2.h
+++ b/src/lib/crypto/builtin/sha2/sha2.h
@@ -46,6 +46,8 @@
 #define SHA384_BLOCK_SIZE 128
 #define SHA512_BLOCK_SIZE 128

+#ifdef K5_BUILTIN_SHA2
+
 struct sha256state {
   unsigned int sz[2];
   uint32_t counter[8];
@@ -75,4 +77,6 @@ void k5_sha512_init(SHA512_CTX *);
 void k5_sha512_update(SHA512_CTX *, const void *, size_t);
 void k5_sha512_final(void *, SHA512_CTX *);

+#endif /* K5_BUILTIN_SHA2 */
+
 #endif /* SHA2_H */
